# Intuition
<!-- Describe your first thoughts on how to solve this problem. -->
Traverse both linked lists simultaneously and add their node values and store the result in a new linked list.
# Approach
<!-- Describe your approach to solving the problem. -->
- The solution iterates through the linked lists l1 and l2 until both linked lists are null, and the sum is greater than 0. 

- In each iteration, the sum is calculated by adding the values of the current nodes of l1 and l2 and the carry from the previous iteration.

- If the sum is greater than or equal to 10, the carry over is calculated and the sum is reduced by 10. 

- A new node is created with the value of sum and is added to the result linked list using the head pointer. 

- The head pointer is then moved to the next node in the result linked list. 

- The sum is then set to the carry and carry is set to 0 for the next iteration. 

- The result linked list is returned after the loop terminates.
# Complexity
- Time complexity:
<!-- Add your time complexity here, e.g. $$O(n)$$ -->
The time complexity of this solution is O(max(m,n)), where m and n are the lengths of the two linked lists.

- Space complexity:
<!-- Add your space complexity here, e.g. $$O(n)$$ -->
The space complexity of this solution is O(max(m,n)), where m and n are the lengths of the two linked lists.
# Code
```
/**
 * Definition for singly-linked list.
 * function ListNode(val, next) {
 *     this.val = (val===undefined ? 0 : val)
 *     this.next = (next===undefined ? null : next)
 * }
 */
/**
 * @param {ListNode} l1
 * @param {ListNode} l2
 * @return {ListNode}
 */
var addTwoNumbers = function(l1, l2) {
    var List = new ListNode(0);
    var head = List;
    var sum = 0;
    var carry = 0;

    while(l1 !== null || l2 !== null || sum > 0){
        if (l1 !== null) {
            sum += l1.val;
            l1 = l1.next;
        }
        if (l2 !== null) {
            sum += l2.val;
            l2 = l2.next;
        }
        if (sum >= 10) {
            carry = 1;
            sum -= 10;
        }
      //  console.log(head.val);
        head.val = sum;

       // console.log(head.val);

        if (l1 !== null || l2 !== null || carry > 0) {
            head.next = new ListNode(carry);
            head = head.next;
        }

        sum = carry;
        carry = 0;
    }

    return List;
};

```

