Solution: 
Because digits of the number are stored in reverse order, we can add each digit from the left to right.
But we need to pay attention to a situation that the sum is bigger than 9. So, we can set a variable-carry to record if there is a sum bigger than 9.
After add each node, don't forget to check if carry > 0, we need to add one more node into our output.
TC: O(n)
SC: O(1), space complexity means extra space. The data structure that needed to be returned is not the extra space.

```
public ListNode add(ListNode l1, ListNode l2) {
    if (l1 == null) {
        return l2;
    } else if (l2 == null) {
        return l1;
    }
    int sum = 0;
    int carry = 0;
    ListNode dummy = new ListNode(0);
    ListNode curr = dummy;
    while (l1 != null || l2 != null) {
        int x = l1 == null ? 0 : l1.val;
        int y = l2 == null ? 0 : l2.val;
        sum = x + y + carry;
        carry = sum / 10;
        curr.next = new ListNode(sum % 10);
        curr = curr.next;
